	<TD WIDTH="100%" HEIGHT="40">
            <FONT SIZE="4" FACE="Lucida Grande,Helvetica,Arial">
            <B>I get an invalid video mode with Quake and/or QuakeWorld</B>
            </FONT>
        </TD>
    </TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="7">
    <TR>
	<TD>
            <P>
            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">
            If you get a video mode, which your monitor can't display upon the first start of Quake, you should do the following:
            </FONT>
            </P>
        </TD>
    </TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="7" BGCOLOR="#ffffcc">
    <TR VALIGN="top" BGCOLOR="#ffffcc">
	<TD BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" WIDTH="98%">
            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">
                <TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="3">
                    <TR VALIGN="top">
                        <TD WIDTH="16">
                            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Helvetica,Arial">
                            <B>1</B>
                            </FONT>
                        </TD>
                        <TD>
                            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">
                            Open &quot;TextEdit&quot; which comes with the MacOS X installation.
                            </FONT>
                        </TD>
                    </TR>
                </TABLE>
                <TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="3">
                    <TR VALIGN="top">
                        <TD WIDTH="16">
                            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Helvetica,Arial">
                            <B>2</B>
                            </FONT>
                        </TD>
                        <TD>
                            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">
                            Locate the file &quot;config.cfg&quot; inside your &quot;id1&quot; folder and open it with &quot;TextEdit&quot;.
                            </FONT>
                        </TD>
                    </TR>
                </TABLE>
                <TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="3">
                    <TR VALIGN="top">
                        <TD WIDTH="16">
                            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Helvetica,Arial">
                            <B>3</B>
                            </FONT>
                        </TD>
                        <TD>
                            <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Lucida Grande,Geneva,Arial">
                            Edit the line &quot;_vid_default_mode x&quot; within the &quot;id1/config.cfg&quot; file and change the value of "x" until you get a working display mode. For example: &quot;_vid_default_mode 0&quot;. Mode &quot;0&quot;, &quot;1&quot; and &quot;2&quot; are windowed modes.
                            </FONT>
                        </TD>
                    </TR>
                </TABLE>
             </FONT>
	</TD>
    </TR>
